  "text": "Plasma TNF-␣ Levels. It has been shown that the plasma concentrations of inflammatory mediators such as TNF-␣ are increased in the insulin-resistant diabetic state, and that the reduction of the levels of TNF-␣ in diabetic mice correlates with increased insulin sensitivity and decreased plasma insulin and blood glucose levels [CITATION_1] . Therefore, we determined the effects of the ␣7 agonist on obesity-induced levels of plasma TNF-␣. TC-7020-treated and untreated lean db ϩ mice showed no change in the plasma levels of TNF-␣, but obese db Ϫ mice had elevated fasting plasma TNF-␣ levels. When the db Ϫ obese mice were treated with TC-7020, they displayed significantly decreased plasma TNF-␣ levels compared with their vehicle-treated controls (p Ͻ 0.05). However, levels did not return to those of lean controls. The decrease was blocked by the ␣7 antagonist MLA (Fig. 1) , implicating the involvement of ␣7 nAChRs.",
